                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16371",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I Disagree.\n\nThe reason is that a Zend_Http_Response object is not instantiated (and should not be)  if there is no _HTTP_ response. \n\nSince there is no connection, there is no HTTP request and no HTTP response, so there cannot be a call to $response->isSuccessful() method.\n\n$response->isSuccessful() \/ ->isError() etc. relate to the _HTTP_ response code, not to some networking or other related issues.\n\nYou should (and can, very easily) use try \/ catch in your code to make sure there are no networking issues. \n\nIf you think this should be further discussed, please submit to fw-webserives@lists.zend.com and take the discussion there, so everyone can participate. \n\nI am closing this bug for now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-08-20T10:30:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-08-20T10:30:06.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
